cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV

This paper deals with text document classification using a combination of traditional feature engineering and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and automatic feature engineering, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively. Finally, the paper also involves the use of image processing techniques for text classification, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
